      "acceptanceCriteria": "Characterisation of operator-introduced input errors (e.g., incorrect flow-rate targets, speed settings, dimensional inputs) and their effect on model outputs and clinical decisions.",
      "rationale": "A single use-error scenario (entry of flow rate in mL/min instead of L/min) was noted in the hazard log but not propagated through the model. Systematic characterisation of perfusionist and clinical engineering operator error modes — including speed misentry, incorrect patient weight-indexed flow targets, and dimensional tolerance misreading — was not performed. No sensitivity analysis on erroneous inputs was conducted. The factor is recorded as not-assessed; the gap is acknowledged but no structured use-error evaluation or human factors validation activity was linked to this COU."
    },
